title: iso13818-1.pdf
description:
ISO/IEC 13818 Part 1: Systems, second edition 2000-12-01

Information technology - 
Generic coding of moving pictures and associated audio information:
System

====================================================================

This is an ISO/IEC standard describing how MPEG audio and video
is encapsulated in in a Transport Stream (TS - used by HDTV)
or a Program Stream )PS - used by DVD and just about all MPEG files).

For some strange reason ISO wants you to comply with this standard
but refuses to let you download it but wants to sell it to you instead.

Bah humbug!
